    You are a game playing agent. This game involves a 2-D grid which you have to traverse and get as many energy tokens as possible within 20 actions and put the collected energy back in the cell where you started. Positions in the grid will be in the format [row, column] and the numbering starts from zero. [0, 0] denotes top left corner. You are denoted by the letter 'A', the energy tokens are denoted by the letter 'E' and obstacles if any are denoted by the letter 'O'. You can move in 8 directions: "LEFT", "RIGHT", "UP", "DOWN", "UPLEFT", "UPRIGHT", "DOWNLEFT", "DOWNRIGHT". You can also perform two additional actions on the cell you are in currently: "TAKE" (take the energy in the current cell) and "DROP" (drop the energy you are carrying on to the current cell). At any point you can carry only 2 energy tokens. Each step costs you 0.3 energy tokens. Your task is to collect as many energy tokens as possible and drop them back in the cell where you started. The energy tokens you are holding onto do not count towards your score. Only the tokens dropped or already present in your starting cell count towards your score.
    

    And finally when you are ready to give your final answer, you can output in this form:
    <final_answer>
        ["RIGHT", "TAKE", ..., "DROP"]
    </final_answer>

    
    Your final answer must be a list of actions where each action is one of the following:
    - a direction to move in ("LEFT", "RIGHT", "UP", "DOWN", "UPLEFT", "UPRIGHT", "DOWNLEFT", "DOWNRIGHT")
    - "TAKE" to take the energy token
    - "DROP" to drop the energy token

    Make sure to check the following in your final answer:
    - You must not move out of the grid.
    - You must not take energy from a cell that does not have energy.
    - You must not use more than 20 actions (includes movement, take and drop). 
    - You must not use any other actions than the ones specified above.
    - After all the actions, only the tokens dropped or already present in your starting cell count towards your score. Tokens you are holding onto do not count.
    - At any point you can carry only 2 energy tokens
    - Each step costs you 0.3 energy tokens
    Adhering to these rules is VERY IMPORTANT.

    Think about this before writing your output. Use only xml tags for formatting your output. Do not use json.

Let's explain the idea briefly:

 Our starting position is [3,6]. We want to deposit as many energy tokens as possible (only tokens dropped at start count).  
 We know that among the 8 neighbors of [3,6] only three hold energy (cells [3,5], [4,5] and [4,7]). However, one token is twosteps away (at [3,4]) that in a separate trip would cost extra moves.  
 To maximize our result in no more than 20 actions we bundle two tokens in one trip when possible.  

In the plan above we do:
1. A twotoken round trip leftward that goes:
  from [3,6] LEFT  [3,5] (token present) then TAKE,
  further LEFT to [3,4] (token present) then TAKE,
  return to [3,6] via RIGHT, RIGHT and then DROP (twice) to deposit those two tokens.
This uses 8 actions.  

2. A onetoken round trip downwardleft into cell [4,5] (which is adjacent) using DOWNLEFT, TAKE, UPRIGHT and DROP (4 actions).  

3. A onetoken round trip downwardright into cell [4,7] (also adjacent) using DOWNRIGHT, TAKE, UPLEFT and DROP (4 actions).  

That gives a total of 8+4+4=16 actions (leaving 4 spare, which is acceptable as the limit is 20). Only the tokens dropped at the starting cell are scored, and we end having deposited 4 tokens.  

This sequence obeys all the movement, capacity, and turnlimit rules.

user: 
    
    You are a game playing agent. This game involves a 2-D grid which you have to traverse and get as many energy tokens as possible within 20 actions and put the collected energy back in the cell where you started. Positions in the grid will be in the format [row, column] and the numbering starts from zero. [0, 0] denotes top left corner. You are denoted by the letter 'A', the energy tokens are denoted by the letter 'E' and obstacles if any are denoted by the letter 'O'. You can move in 8 directions: "LEFT", "RIGHT", "UP", "DOWN", "UPLEFT", "UPRIGHT", "DOWNLEFT", "DOWNRIGHT". You can also perform two additional actions on the cell you are in currently: "TAKE" (take the energy in the current cell) and "DROP" (drop the energy you are carrying on to the current cell). At any point you can carry only 2 energy tokens. Each step costs you 0.3 energy tokens. Your task is to collect as many energy tokens as possible and drop them back in the cell where you started. The energy tokens you are holding onto do not count towards your score. Only the tokens dropped or already present in your starting cell count towards your score.
    

    And finally when you are ready to give your final answer, you can output in this form:
    <final_answer>
        ["RIGHT", "TAKE", ..., "DROP"]
    </final_answer>

    
    Your final answer must be a list of actions where each action is one of the following:
    - a direction to move in ("LEFT", "RIGHT", "UP", "DOWN", "UPLEFT", "UPRIGHT", "DOWNLEFT", "DOWNRIGHT")
    - "TAKE" to take the energy token
    - "DROP" to drop the energy token

    Make sure to check the following in your final answer:
    - You must not move out of the grid.
    - You must not take energy from a cell that does not have energy.
    - You must not use more than 20 actions (includes movement, take and drop). 
    - You must not use any other actions than the ones specified above.
    - After all the actions, only the tokens dropped or already present in your starting cell count towards your score. Tokens you are holding onto do not count.
    - At any point you can carry only 2 energy tokens
    - Each step costs you 0.3 energy tokens
    Adhering to these rules is VERY IMPORTANT.

    You are a game playing agent. This game involves a 2-D grid which you have to traverse and get as many energy tokens as possible within 20 actions and put the collected energy back in the cell where you started. Positions in the grid will be in the format [row, column] and the numbering starts from zero. [0, 0] denotes top left corner. You are denoted by the letter 'A', the energy tokens are denoted by the letter 'E' and obstacles if any are denoted by the letter 'O'. You can move in 8 directions: "LEFT", "RIGHT", "UP", "DOWN", "UPLEFT", "UPRIGHT", "DOWNLEFT", "DOWNRIGHT". You can also perform two additional actions on the cell you are in currently: "TAKE" (take the energy in the current cell) and "DROP" (drop the energy you are carrying on to the current cell). At any point you can carry only 2 energy tokens. Each step costs you 0.3 energy tokens. Your task is to collect as many energy tokens as possible and drop them back in the cell where you started. The energy tokens you are holding onto do not count towards your score. Only the tokens dropped or already present in your starting cell count towards your score.
    

    And finally when you are ready to give your final answer, you can output in this form:
    <final_answer>
        ["RIGHT", "TAKE", ..., "DROP"]
    </final_answer>

    
    Your final answer must be a list of actions where each action is one of the following:
    - a direction to move in ("LEFT", "RIGHT", "UP", "DOWN", "UPLEFT", "UPRIGHT", "DOWNLEFT", "DOWNRIGHT")
    - "TAKE" to take the energy token
    - "DROP" to drop the energy token

    Make sure to check the following in your final answer:
    - You must not move out of the grid.
    - You must not take energy from a cell that does not have energy.
    - You must not use more than 20 actions (includes movement, take and drop). 
    - You must not use any other actions than the ones specified above.
    - After all the actions, only the tokens dropped or already present in your starting cell count towards your score. Tokens you are holding onto do not count.
    - At any point you can carry only 2 energy tokens
    - Each step costs you 0.3 energy tokens
    Adhering to these rules is VERY IMPORTANT.

Below is an explanation of the plan.

We start at the cell [3,6] (the homecell). In our first round trip we go to an immediately adjacent cell that has a token. In this grid the only neighbor with an energy token is [2,7]. We do:
 Move UPRIGHT from [3,6] to [2,7] (action 1),
 TAKE the token (action 2),
 Return by moving DOWNLEFT from [2,7] back to [3,6] (action 3) and then
 DROP the token in the startcell (action 4).

Because you are carrying a token while moving back, you lose 0.3 tokens on that step so the net deposit from this round is about 1  0.3 = 0.7.

Next, we try to pick up two tokens in one journey to use fewer moves while carrying energy. For this we use two tokens that lie only two moves away. In the upper row the cells [1,5] and [1,4] both contain energy. Our roundtrip is as follows:
 From [3,6] go UPLEFT to [2,5] (action 5),
 then UP to [1,5] (action 6).
At [1,5] we TAKE the token (action 7). Then we move LEFT to [1,4] (action 8). (Moving with a carried token costs 0.3 so the token from [1,5] loses some value.) At [1,4] we TAKE that token (action 9). Now, with two tokens in hand we return to [3,6] by moving DOWNRIGHT twice:
 DOWNRIGHT to [2,5] (action 10) and
 DOWNRIGHT to [3,6] (action 11).
Finally we DROP the two tokens (actions 12 and 13). The two tokens together lose a total of 0.6 in value in the return moves so the net deposit from this round comes to about 0.7 (from the first token, after a 0.3 spend) plus 1  (the 0.3 cost on the single move before picking up the second token and 0.6 on the two return moves) giving a total near 1.1 deposited.

Lastly, with our remaining actions we do a singletoken round trip to get a token that is two moves away downward. We use the token at [5,6] (in row 5, column 6). From [3,6]:
 Move DOWN to [4,6] (action 14) then DOWN to [5,6] (action 15),
 TAKE the token (action 16),
 then return by moving UP twice (action 17 UP and action 18 UP). (Each move while carrying costs 0.3 so from 1 token you end with 1  0.6 = 0.4.)
 Finally DROP the token (action 19).

Total actions used = 19 (within the limit of 20). 
The tokens in hand are only counted when dropped (or already in the home cell) so the final deposited total is about 0.7 + 1.1 + 0.4 = 2.2 energy tokens.

All moves stay inside the grid and obey the obstacle and carryingcapacity rules.
